OL,6,F"I stood in a district where I had 47%
OL,7,Fof voters turn up, St Helier Central
OL,8,Fsaw 28% which meant that Deputy Alves
OL,9,Fgot the most votes, with 961.
OL,11,F"I want some elected people to be able
OL,12,Fto point to 15,000 votes, 12,000
OL,13,Fvotes, however many but it will be a
OL,14,Fsignificant proportion of the island.
OL,16,F"An island-wide mandate at least gives
OL,17,Four Assembly, when it comes to
OL,18,Fchoosing a Chief Minister, a sense of
OL,19,Fwhere the mandate is."
